title.narrative: UN Secondment to coordinate Nepal Risk Reduction Consortium

description.narrative: This activity (UN Secondment to coordinate Nepal Risk Reduction Consortium) is a component of UK Support to Increase Resilience to Natural Disasters in Nepal reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £1,321,736. This component benefits Nepal, and works in the following sector(s): Environmental policy and administrative management, Material relief assistance and services , Disaster prevention and preparedness. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited. The start date is 26-04-2011 and the end date is 30-09-2016.
